overview: The user initiated a project to enhance an existing sleep
  questionnaire application by integrating a database and an admin dashboard.
  The primary goal was to store questionnaire responses, enable CSV data export,
  and provide a secure, simple interface for client access. The approach
  involved updating the Prisma schema to include a
  model, creating dedicated API endpoints for data submission and retrieval, and
  developing a basic admin dashboard. A key decision was to simplify the
  authentication system from a custom HMAC-signed session to a more
  straightforward Next.js middleware-based approach, using a single admin
  password and a simple cookie for session management. This change was made to
  ensure the simplest possible solution while still providing necessary security
  for the admin panel. The chosen database was NeonDB (PostgreSQL), which
  seamlessly integrated with Prisma.
